                            <comment id="17087049" author="reta" created="Sun, 19 Apr 2020 15:24:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mattzek&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mattzek&quot;&gt;mattzek&lt;/a&gt; ,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe your expectations are correct, as per section 4.5.2 of the JAX-RS 2.1 specification, the ResponseProcessingException should be thrown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; When a provider method throws an exception, the JAX-RS client runtime will map it to an instance of&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; ProcessingException if thrown while processing a request, and to a ResponseProcessingException&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; if thrown while processing a response.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks like an issue on CXF side. &lt;br/&gt;
Thank you for reporting it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Best Regards,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160; Andriy Redko&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
